Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Administration of
Criminal Justice to the original bill:
1. Remove human trafficking and trafficking of children for sexual purposes as
offenses when a consideration of the court is needed for conditions of release.
2. Clarify that the defendant is restricted from participating in certain occupations
for work, rather than employment.
3. Remove the proposed law requirement that the court consider the previous
criminal history of the defendant and whether the defendant poses a threat or
danger to the public in determining the work restrictions of the defendant.
4. Require the court, as a condition of bail, to prohibit a defendant alleged to have
committed human trafficking or trafficking of children for sexual purposes from
going to the victim's residence or household, school, or place of employment, or
from otherwise contacting the victim in any manner.
5. Make technical changes.
